text: Dieter Kemper (11 August 1937 – 11 October 2018) was a German cyclist. He competed professionally between 1961 and 1980. During his career he won one UCI Motor-paced World Championships in 1975, seven European titlesEuropameisterschaften. Stayer.de and 26 six-day road races. He finished three times in third place at world championships.
